The paper deals with a crowdsourcing model and peer prediction, which are both topics that fall under the umbrella of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of machine learning algorithms to curate the dataset also suggests that this paper could be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves the manipulation of data, which is a topic that falls under data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The use of incentives to encourage honest behavior among workers is a topic that falls under social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper involves the use of information theory to analyze the performance of the algorithm, which suggests that it could be categorized under information theory (cs.IT).
